00:19.644 --> 00:21.730
♪ I GOT THE BEAT SO ALL THE KIDS
DANCE WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:22.105 --> 00:25.775
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:26.025 --> 00:29.696
[♪...]

00:29.946 --> 00:31.614
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:31.865 --> 00:33.575
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B. ♪

00:33.825 --> 00:35.577
[MUSIC ENDS]

00:37.078 --> 00:39.497
{\an8}Captioning Provided By:
MTV NETWORKS

00:39.748 --> 00:44.461
[♪...]

00:48.089 --> 00:50.842
{\an1}NOW, GIRLS,<i> THIS</i> IS A MUSHROOM
AND <i> THIS</i> IS A TOADSTOOL.

00:50.925 --> 00:53.553
THERE'S NO WAY OF TELLING THEM
APART, THEY LOOK EXACTLY ALIKE

00:53.803 --> 00:56.639
ONLY ONE IS HORRIBLY POISONOUS.

00:56.890 --> 00:57.932
SO DON'T EAT THAT ONE.

00:58.266 --> 01:00.477
REMEMBER, ONLY EAT THIS ONE.

01:00.727 --> 01:02.312
OH, WAIT A MINUTE.

01:02.562 --> 01:03.813
{\an1}EAT THIS ONE,
BUT DON'T EAT THAT ONE.

01:03.897 --> 01:05.147
WHAT'S WRONG, GWEN?

01:05.397 --> 01:07.150
UH, I DON'T KNOW.

01:07.400 --> 01:08.818
OOH, IT ITCHES EVERYWHERE

01:12.322 --> 01:13.823
[GASPS]

01:13.907 --> 01:15.533
ATTENTION, ATTENTION, EVERYONE.

01:15.784 --> 01:16.910
ATTEMPT TO REMAIN CALM.

01:17.243 --> 01:18.953
THIS IS A POISON IVY ALERT.

01:19.037 --> 01:21.873
I REPEAT, POISON IVY ALERT.

01:22.123 --> 01:24.542
STAY BACK, WE DON'T WANT
AN EPIDEMIC.

01:24.793 --> 01:27.253
{\an1}WHAT WE DON'T WANT
IS AN AMATEUR DIAGNOSIS.

01:27.504 --> 01:31.633
{\an1}I'LL BE THE ONE TO DECLARE
EPIDEMICS, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

01:31.883 --> 01:34.844
{\an1}[GASPS] BESSIE, YOU'VE
NEVER BEEN WRONG-ER.

01:35.136 --> 01:37.180
{\an1}THIS IS HARDLY POISON IVY,
IT'S... CHICKEN POX.

01:40.141 --> 01:42.602
EVERYONE, FREEZE.

01:42.852 --> 01:45.980
{\an5}ANY BEE WHO DOES NOT HAVE
HER CHICKEN POX BADGE,
IDENTIFY YOURSELF.

01:46.064 --> 01:47.315
GOT IT.

01:47.565 --> 01:48.566
GOT IT.

01:48.817 --> 01:49.859
GOT IT.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.027
GOBBLE-GOBBLE.

01:51.110 --> 01:52.654
[GRUNTS]

01:52.904 --> 01:54.989
DON'T GOT IT.

01:55.073 --> 01:56.407
GIVE IT.

01:56.658 --> 01:58.034
POX ME, I NEED THAT BADGE.

01:58.117 --> 01:59.244
[SCREAMING]

02:01.663 --> 02:03.748
COME ON, GWEN, HELP A BEE OUT.

02:03.998 --> 02:05.166
SHARING IS CARING. [GRUNTS]

02:05.416 --> 02:06.543
OH, GET AWAY.

02:06.793 --> 02:08.877
NO, BESSIE, DOWN.

02:09.211 --> 02:11.756
THERE WILL BE NO
CROSS-INFECTIONS ON MY WATCH.

02:12.006 --> 02:14.259
{\an3}BUT MRS. GIBBONS, THIS CHANCE
MAY NEVER COME ALONG AGAIN.

02:14.509 --> 02:16.427
{\an3}I MEAN, I'M NOT
GETTING ANY YOUNGER.

02:16.678 --> 02:19.472
{\an3}HERE, YOU PEOPLE
LIKE HUGGING THESE.

02:19.722 --> 02:22.725
{\an3}COME ALONG, GWEN, I WILL BE
KIND ENOUGH TO DRIVE YOU HOME.

02:25.812 --> 02:27.814
NOW BE SURE TO WAVE TO ME
ONCE YOU'RE SAFELY INSIDE.

02:33.903 --> 02:36.072
GET READY TO GIVE UP THE COUCH.

02:36.155 --> 02:37.323
[GROANS] I'M SICK.

02:39.701 --> 02:40.159
[COUGHS]

02:42.620 --> 02:45.665
AW, I'VE GOTTA SHARE THIS, TOO?

02:45.915 --> 02:48.167
[DOORBELL RINGS]

02:48.418 --> 02:49.919
{\an3}[WHISTLING]

02:50.003 --> 02:51.963
OH, HI, GWEN.

02:52.297 --> 02:53.423
{\an3}I'LL MAKE THIS QUICK,
'CAUSE I'M SURE YOU'RE TIRED.

02:53.506 --> 02:54.841
{\an3}OH...

02:55.091 --> 02:57.302
THE WHOLE FAMILY SICK.

02:57.552 --> 03:01.806
HOW CONVENIENT...
-LY UNFORTUNATE.

03:02.056 --> 03:04.100
[CLEARS THROAT]

03:04.183 --> 03:06.102
AS YOU KNOW, I AM CURRENTLY
THE ONLY MEMBER OF TROOP 828

03:06.394 --> 03:08.104
{\an3}WHO HAS NOT RECEIVED
THE CHICKEN POX BADGE.

03:08.396 --> 03:09.981
{\an3}YOU CAN IMAGINE
MY EMBARRASSMENT.

03:10.064 --> 03:12.650
SO HERE'S WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO.

03:12.901 --> 03:14.027
{\an6}IF YOU DON'T MIND,
I'M JUST GONNA TOUCH ALL YOUR
CHICKEN POX REAL FAST

03:14.360 --> 03:15.695
AND THEN I'LL BE ON MY WAY.

03:15.945 --> 03:17.947
EW, NASTY, BACK...

03:18.031 --> 03:20.491
OK, OK, OK, JUST COUGH ON ME.

03:20.575 --> 03:22.410
{\an1}...OFF.

03:22.660 --> 03:24.162
UGH.

03:24.412 --> 03:26.915
[DOORBELL RINGS]

03:27.165 --> 03:29.125
{\an3}DID SOMEBODY ORDER
A LARGE MEATS <i> AMORE?</i>

03:29.375 --> 03:31.169
[SNIFFS] MM...

03:31.419 --> 03:33.963
UGH, YOU'RE SICK.

03:34.047 --> 03:35.214
I'M TRYING.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.345
PLUNGE PATROL.

03:40.595 --> 03:41.971
[GRUNTING]

03:47.060 --> 03:49.145
YEAH, I GOT A CALL THAT
YOUR CABLE WAS OUT.

03:49.228 --> 03:51.397
SHOULD BE FINE, ONCE I
COME INSIDE FOR A FEW MINUTES

03:51.648 --> 03:53.983
AND, YOU KNOW, TOUCH EVERYTHING-
FREE MOVIE CHANNELS.

03:54.067 --> 03:55.985
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:01.699 --> 04:03.952
I'D LIKE TO INVITE YOU
TO A VEGETARIAN FEAST.

04:04.202 --> 04:06.454
{\an3}JUST CHECK YES OR NO
WITH YOUR TONGUE.

04:06.704 --> 04:08.081
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:08.373 --> 04:11.042
THAT'S IT, STINKENBOTTOM.

04:11.125 --> 04:14.837
[WHEEZES] JUST GO TO... GO TO...

04:15.088 --> 04:18.382
[GRUNTS] GO TO YOUR OWN HOUSE
OR GARBAGE CAN OR SOMETHING.

04:18.632 --> 04:20.969
JUST LEAVE... GO... ALONE.

04:21.219 --> 04:22.762
Bessie: HOW DO YOU KNOW IT'S ME?

04:27.642 --> 04:30.353
[SCOFFS] EVERYONE KNOWS IT'S
A STUPID CONSOLATION BADGE.

04:30.603 --> 04:34.148
{\an1}MOM, ARE YOU SURE I'VE
NEVER HAD THE CHICKEN POX?

04:34.482 --> 04:37.860
HONEY, MY ANSWER HASN'T CHANGED
IN THE LAST 30 SECONDS.

04:38.111 --> 04:40.196
BEN- YES, YOU- NO.

04:40.279 --> 04:42.490
LUCKY GWEN.

04:42.740 --> 04:45.076
I DON'T SEE WHY SHE WON'T SHARE
HER POX WITH ME, REAL SELFISH...

04:45.159 --> 04:47.036
{\an3}LUCKY?

04:47.120 --> 04:48.997
{\an3}THE POOR THING
MUST BE MISERABLE.

04:49.330 --> 04:51.749
{\an3}I KNOW, WHY DON'T YOU
MAKE HER A NICE CARE PACKAGE?

04:52.000 --> 04:54.544
HUH, THERE MUST BE
A BADGE FOR THAT.

04:54.794 --> 04:59.424
{\an5}OH, MOM, THERE ISN'T
A BADGE FOR EVERYTHING,
I'VE TOLD YOU A MILLION TIMES.

04:59.674 --> 05:02.218
[GRUNTING AND STRAINING AUDIBLY]

05:02.301 --> 05:03.761
[SQUEALS]

05:04.012 --> 05:07.140
[HUMMING]

05:07.390 --> 05:10.226
OW, OH...

05:10.310 --> 05:14.355
{\an5}OH, YES, HELLO, HELLO,
THIS IS BENJAMIN HIGGENBOTTOM,
FREELANCE SIDEKICK.

05:14.605 --> 05:17.066
BEN, THE TIME HAS COME
FOR YOU TO SERVE THE MIGHTY B.

05:17.150 --> 05:19.110
Meet me in the hive
in 0-500 seconds.

05:19.193 --> 05:22.071
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

05:22.155 --> 05:23.948
BENJAMIN, I'M GONNA
SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

05:24.198 --> 05:26.576
SOMETHING SECRET AND AWESOME.

05:26.826 --> 05:30.705
{\an6}BUT FIRST YOU HAVE TO
SWEAR TO ACCEPT THIS
SUPER-IMPORTANT MISSION.

05:30.955 --> 05:32.957
I SWEAR, I SWEAR,
SHOW ME, SHOW ME.

05:33.207 --> 05:33.583
[GRUNTS]

05:43.801 --> 05:47.972
Ben: WHOA, WHAT IS THIS?

05:48.222 --> 05:52.226
Bessie: THIS, MY TRIAL-SIDEKICK,
IS EXACTLY WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE...

05:52.310 --> 05:54.979
A CHICKEN POX BUNKER.

05:55.229 --> 05:57.106
IT CAN BE MODIFIED TO
ACCOMMODATE MUMPS AND MEASLES.

05:57.398 --> 05:59.150
BUT YOU'RE NOT SICK.

05:59.233 --> 06:00.985
{\an1}EXACTLY.

06:01.235 --> 06:03.279
{\an1}CURSED WITH A SUPERIOR
IMMUNE SYSTEM

06:03.362 --> 06:05.531
I STAYED HEALTHY WHEN ALL THE
OTHER PRE-SCHOOLERS TOOK ILL.

06:05.782 --> 06:08.868
{\an1}I'VE WAITED FIVE LONG YEARS
FOR ANOTHER CHICKEN POX OUTBREAK

06:09.118 --> 06:11.204
{\an1}AND THIS ONE IS NOT
PASSING ME BY.

06:11.537 --> 06:13.122
THAT'S WHERE YOU COME IN.

06:13.456 --> 06:15.166
I'M READY, WHAT'S MY MISSION?

06:15.458 --> 06:17.835
CARE PACKAGE,
HAND-DELIVERED TO GWEN.

06:18.086 --> 06:20.338
BUT I DON'T WANT TO GO TO
A SICK PERSON'S HOUSE.

06:20.588 --> 06:22.632
YOU HAVE TO, BEN.

06:22.882 --> 06:24.759
{\an1}YOU ALREADY HAD THE CHICKEN POX,
SO YOU CAN'T GET IT AGAIN.

06:25.009 --> 06:26.677
DON'T YOU SEE?

06:26.928 --> 06:29.138
YOU'RE INDESTRUCTIBLE.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.974
{\an1}AND BESIDES, I CAN'T TRUST
A MISSION LIKE THIS TO A DOG.

06:35.061 --> 06:36.979
[LAUGHS] FOUR-LEGS.

06:41.442 --> 06:43.027
NICE DRESS.

06:43.277 --> 06:45.154
IT IS A SMOCK.

06:45.238 --> 06:47.740
AND THIS IS A CARE PACKAGE.

06:57.625 --> 07:02.672
[BESSIE GRUNTS]

07:06.968 --> 07:10.471
{\an5}SO THEN WHEN THERE'S
JUST ENOUGH WATER TO COVER
THE BOTTOM OF THE TUB

07:10.721 --> 07:13.683
{\an6}YOU POUR IN ONE CUP
OF THE OATMEAL AND THEN
STIR IT EVERY 10 SECONDS.

07:13.933 --> 07:16.310
[COUGHING]

07:43.045 --> 07:45.298
Ben: WHEN I GOT IT,
I HAD IT FOR, LIKE, SIX MONTHS.

07:45.631 --> 07:46.799
AND I HAD A FEVER OF 112.

07:53.723 --> 07:55.308
[GRUNTS]

07:55.600 --> 07:56.100
[FROG CROAKS]

08:04.609 --> 08:07.612
AH.

08:09.989 --> 08:12.992
I DON'T REMEMBER ANY OF IT,
'CAUSE I ALSO GOT AMNESIA.

08:13.242 --> 08:16.871
SO BASICALLY I'M IMMUNE,
YOU KNOW, INDESTRUCTIBLE?

08:17.121 --> 08:18.789
OH, LET ME GET THAT FOR YOU.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.375
HEY, IT'S LIKE CONNECT-THE-DOTS.

08:21.459 --> 08:23.920
THERE'S A BUNNY... AND A HAT.

08:24.170 --> 08:24.670
OOH, AND THERE'S THE BIG DIPPER.

08:30.009 --> 08:32.345
[LAUGHS]

08:37.683 --> 08:38.808
[SCREAMING]

08:38.893 --> 08:40.645
[GRUNTS]

08:45.733 --> 08:46.734
WHAT, HUH?

08:46.984 --> 08:48.027
[SCREAMS]

08:53.366 --> 08:56.285
{\an3}UH, AND THAT'S WHY
YOU SHOULD NEVER PICK A SCAB.

08:56.369 --> 08:56.661
HAVE A NICE DAY, BYE.

09:03.626 --> 09:08.297
98.6, 98.6 AND A 10th.

09:08.589 --> 09:11.300
THAT'S GOOD,
TEMPERATURE CLIMBING.

09:11.384 --> 09:13.469
BEN, I'M ALMOST FEVERISH.

09:13.552 --> 09:18.766
I REQUIRE A GRILLED CHEESE
SANDWICH SANS CRUST.

09:19.016 --> 09:20.935
AND A GLASS OF ORANGE JUICE,
FRESH-SQUEEZED, IF YOU PLEASE.

09:21.185 --> 09:22.311
HEY, THAT RHYMES.

09:22.645 --> 09:24.730
BRING ME MY ILLNESS JOURNAL

09:24.981 --> 09:26.732
SO I MAY RECORD THE POETRY
OF MY SUFFERING.

09:26.983 --> 09:29.151
[GROANS]

09:29.402 --> 09:31.487
Bessie: AND YOU KNOW WHAT'S
REALLY GOOD FOR CHICKEN POX?

09:31.570 --> 09:33.614
WATERMELON WITH SEEDS
THAT YOU PICKED OUT BY HAND.

09:33.864 --> 09:36.158
SERVED IN ONE-INCH BALLS.

09:36.409 --> 09:37.868
THAT'S INCH,
NOT CENTIMETER, BEN.

09:38.119 --> 09:40.454
[GROANS]

09:43.207 --> 09:46.752
UGH, MOM, I THINK I'M SICK.

09:47.003 --> 09:48.296
SICK OF BESSIE.

09:48.629 --> 09:50.381
OH, YOU DON'T LOOK SO GOOD.

09:50.673 --> 09:54.176
[GASPS] YOU'RE BURNING UP.

09:54.427 --> 09:56.554
WE BETTER TAKE YOUR TEMPERATURE.

10:00.182 --> 10:01.684
MOM, THIS IS A MEAT THERMOMETER.

10:01.934 --> 10:03.519
WELL, IT WAS WORTH A SHOT.

10:03.811 --> 10:06.522
LET'S SEE IF I CAN
FIND ANOTHER ONE.

10:06.605 --> 10:10.109
{\an5}BEN... I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR
THOSE MELON BALLS
FOR 10 MINUTES.

10:10.359 --> 10:13.279
{\an1}NEED I REMIND YOU
THAT I AM BED-RIDDEN?

10:13.612 --> 10:16.490
BUT... YOU'RE... NOT... SICK.

10:16.741 --> 10:18.200
[GASPS] YET.

10:18.451 --> 10:20.369
I'M NOT SICK <i> YET.</i>

10:20.453 --> 10:23.205
{\an3}WHAT KIND OF BROTHER
TURNS HIS BACK ON HIS OWN SISTER

10:23.456 --> 10:26.917
{\an6}WHO HAS SELFLESSLY AGREED
TO POSSIBLY CONSIDER HIM FOR
SUPERHERO SIDEKICK CANDIDACY

10:27.168 --> 10:30.296
OUT OF A HUGE POOL OF
POTENTIAL APPLICANTS.

10:30.629 --> 10:34.050
[STAMMERING]: POSSIBLY CONSIDER?

10:34.300 --> 10:35.092
[SCREAMS]

10:39.555 --> 10:44.685
{\an1}BEN, HONEY, I FINALLY FOUND
A PROPER THERMOMETER- AI.

10:44.935 --> 10:47.396
{\an3}I THINK I DESERVE
AN EXPLANATION.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.482
HUH.

10:49.815 --> 10:52.068
I GUESS IT WAS <i> BEN</i>
WHO NEVER HAD THE CHICKEN POX.

10:52.318 --> 10:54.653
{\an3}LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT,
I <i> DID</i> HAVE THE CHICKEN POX?

10:54.904 --> 10:56.947
HUH, I GUESS YOU DID.

10:57.198 --> 10:59.325
{\an1}THAT'S RIGHT, WE WERE
LIVING IN MARIN.

10:59.658 --> 11:02.244
I WAS HERDING GOATS AT THE TIME.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.373
YES, THE CHICKEN POX BADGE
IS RETROACTIVELY MINE.

11:05.623 --> 11:09.085
IT'S GONNA RIGHT HERE,
RIGHT HERE.

11:09.335 --> 11:12.421
{\an3}HEY, YOU PROMISED
I WAS INDESTRUCTIBLE

11:12.505 --> 11:13.964
AND YOU GOT ME SICK.

11:14.215 --> 11:16.425
AND I HAD TO BALL MELON.

11:16.509 --> 11:18.344
OK, BEN, OK, BEN, OK, BEN.

11:18.594 --> 11:20.096
I'M GONNA MAKE THIS RIGHT.

11:20.346 --> 11:21.430
{\an1}AS SOON AS I
SEW MY NEW BADGE ON.

11:21.514 --> 11:23.432
[GRUNTS] BEFORE!

11:23.516 --> 11:25.976
TO THE LEFT, NO,
UP A LITTLE MORE.

11:26.227 --> 11:28.187
FASTER, FASTER, SLOW IT DOWN,
SLOW IT DOWN.

11:28.437 --> 11:29.730
DO MY WINGS, DO MY WINGS.

11:29.980 --> 11:31.315
NO, NO, NO, MORE TO THE RIGHT.

11:31.565 --> 11:34.068
OH, THAT'S THE SPOT...

11:35.736 --> 11:38.739
[♪...]

11:57.299 --> 11:59.468
PENNY, WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

11:59.718 --> 12:02.596
{\an4}YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO HELP ME
IDENTIFY SPLIT ENDS
THIS MORNING.

12:02.888 --> 12:04.390
SORRY, PORTIA.

12:04.640 --> 12:07.601
WE GOT CAUGHT UP IN PEANUT-TOSS.

12:07.685 --> 12:09.603
[SCOFFS] LOSER-TASTIC.

12:09.854 --> 12:11.522
WHAT IS THAT?

12:11.814 --> 12:14.358
Bessie: THE HIVE,
YOU'VE SEEN IT BEFORE.

12:14.608 --> 12:17.236
{\an3}WHATEVER, MUST'VE
BLOCKED IT OUT.

12:17.486 --> 12:20.573
{\an3}WELL, IT'S ONLY THE GREATEST
SECRET HIDEOUT EVER.

12:20.906 --> 12:22.992
{\an3}I BUILT IT MYSELF OUT OF
MACARONI AND POPCORN.

12:23.242 --> 12:25.369
DOES IT HAVE A CITY VIEW?

12:25.619 --> 12:27.496
{\an3}YOU CAN SEE ALL THE WAY
ACROSS THE BAY ON A CLEAR DAY.

12:27.580 --> 12:29.582
CENTRAL AIR?

12:29.874 --> 12:31.917
{\an3}HOW ELSE COULD I KEEP THE HIVE
AT AN EVEN 68 DEGREES.

12:32.168 --> 12:34.253
{\an3}LISTEN, I'LL BE HAPPY TO
GIVE YOU A PRIVATE TOUR LATER

12:34.503 --> 12:37.006
BUT RIGHT NOW I'M TRYING TO
BREAK MY PEANUT-TOSS RECORD.

12:37.256 --> 12:41.677
SHE'S GONNA MAKE IT TO 103,
AN ALL-TIME HIGH.

12:41.760 --> 12:43.053
[SCOFFS] BET YOU CAN'T.

12:43.304 --> 12:45.473
UH, NO OFFENSE, PORTIA.

12:45.806 --> 12:48.684
{\an6}BUT I'VE BEEN IN
THE PEANUT-CATCHING GAME
FOR THREE YEARS NOW, SO, UH...

12:48.767 --> 12:50.603
{\an1}OH, YEAH?

12:50.895 --> 12:53.189
{\an1}WELL, ONE WEEKEND AT THE HIVE,
DOUBLE OCCUPANCY...

12:53.439 --> 12:55.483
{\an3}SAYS YOU CAN'T EVEN
MAKE IT TO 100.

12:55.733 --> 12:57.193
[BARKS]

12:57.443 --> 12:58.444
DON'T SWEAT IT, HAPPY.

12:58.777 --> 13:00.696
I GOT THIS LOCKED UP.

13:00.988 --> 13:02.740
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

13:02.990 --> 13:07.119
[GRUNTING]

13:07.369 --> 13:09.788
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

13:10.039 --> 13:12.208
[GRUNTS]

13:12.458 --> 13:13.459
RED LEATHER, YELLOW LEATHER,
RED LEATHER, YELLOW LEATHER.

13:13.709 --> 13:15.544
[ROARS]

13:15.878 --> 13:17.671
RED LEATHER, YELLOW LEATHER,
RED LEATHER, YELLOW LEATHER.

13:18.005 --> 13:19.423
ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO THIS.

13:32.811 --> 13:34.063
[SCREAMS]

13:34.313 --> 13:34.355
[HAPPY BARKS]

13:37.900 --> 13:39.860
KEYS.

13:43.155 --> 13:44.698
OH, AND I'M GONNA EXPECT
TURNDOWN SERVICE.

13:50.829 --> 13:53.165
WELL, MAKE YOURSELVES AT HOME.

13:53.415 --> 13:55.417
{\an4}UM, BUT I JUST FENG SHUI'D
THE PLACE, SO PLEASE,
DON'T MOVE ANYTHING.

13:55.668 --> 13:59.797
[♪...]

13:59.880 --> 14:00.923
[SCREAMS]

14:03.133 --> 14:05.761
{\an3}THAT'S MY HAM RADIO,
I HAVE THE VOLUME SET TO FIVE

14:05.844 --> 14:07.972
WHICH IS OPTIMAL FOR
THE ACOUSTICS IN HERE

14:08.222 --> 14:09.890
SO YOU SHOULDN'T
NEED TO ADJUST IT.

14:10.140 --> 14:11.767
THAT'S THE EMERGENCY
ESCAPE HATCH.

14:12.059 --> 14:13.477
THE LOCK STICKS,
SO TRY NOT TO USE IT

14:13.727 --> 14:14.728
UNLESS YOU REALLY HAVE TO.

14:15.020 --> 14:17.481
UM, WHAT ELSE, UM...

14:17.731 --> 14:19.775
{\an5}THERE'S THE DUMBWAITER
IF YOU WANT TO ORDER UP FROM
MOM'S CAFE.

14:19.858 --> 14:22.403
UH, OH, MY FOSSIL COLLECTION
IS OFF-LIMITS, OF COURSE.

14:22.653 --> 14:25.281
BUT MY HIVE IS YOUR HIVE.

14:25.531 --> 14:27.074
FOR THREE DAYS.

14:27.324 --> 14:29.451
{\an1}AND NOT REALLY,
'CAUSE I BUILT IT.

14:29.702 --> 14:32.037
THIS WALL WOULD LOOK BETTER
WITH PICTURES OF ME ON IT.

14:32.288 --> 14:34.123
[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

14:34.373 --> 14:37.334
THAT'S, OH, BOY,
SPEAKING OF YOU AND MY STUFF

14:37.585 --> 14:40.588
I HAVE DIVIDED THE HIVE
INTO TWO CATEGORIES.

14:40.838 --> 14:45.009
I FLAGGED THINGS THAT
YOU CAN TOUCH IN GREEN

14:45.259 --> 14:48.512
AND THINGS THAT
YOU CAN'T TOUCH IN RED.

14:48.762 --> 14:51.390
AND WITHIN CAN-TOUCH,
THERE IS A SUB-CATEGORY

14:51.640 --> 14:53.225
OF THINGS THAT YOU CAN TOUCH
BUT YOU CAN'T MOVE.

14:53.475 --> 14:55.269
THOSE ARE BLUE.

14:55.519 --> 14:57.229
BUT OF COURSE,
YOU CAN ALWAYS CALL ME.

14:57.479 --> 14:59.648
{\an3}Gwen: ALL RIGHT,
STINKENBOTTOM, GET OUT.

14:59.732 --> 15:02.401
{\an6}I'M SURE YOU GOT
A LOT OF NERD ALARMS
TO SET OFF SOMEWHERE.

15:02.651 --> 15:06.739
{\an4}OH, AND HERE ARE A FEW
LITTLE THINGS I DIDN'T HAVE TIME
TO COVER ON THE TOUR- CALL ME.

15:07.031 --> 15:09.366
I WONDER WHAT
THEY'RE DOING IN THERE.

15:09.617 --> 15:11.744
UGH, WHY HAVEN'T THEY CALLED?

15:12.036 --> 15:14.121
{\an5}OK, KEEP IT TOGETHER,
HIGGENBOTTOM,
YOU NEED TO LET IT GO.

15:14.371 --> 15:18.626
JUST TWO DAYS, 20 HOURS
AND 10 MINUTES TO GO. [GULPS]

15:18.876 --> 15:22.713
{\an5}UGH, WHAT IF THEY'RE, WHAT IF
THEY'RE TOUCHING SOMETHING
IN THE "DON'T TOUCH" CATEGORY?

15:23.047 --> 15:26.175
{\an5}[GASPS] WHAT IF THEY'VE
MOVED SOMETHING IN THE
"TOUCH BUT DON'T MOVE" CATEGORY?

15:26.425 --> 15:28.093
MAYBE I WASN'T CLEAR.

15:28.344 --> 15:29.720
Voices: TOUCH IT,
TOUCH IT, TOUCH IT..

15:29.803 --> 15:32.097
OOH, OOH, OOH...

15:32.348 --> 15:35.976
[DISTORTED WHISPERING...]

15:46.820 --> 15:48.447
Bessie: OH,
GET A HOLD OF YOURSELF.

15:48.697 --> 15:49.907
I CAN'T STAND IT.

15:55.079 --> 15:58.540
{\an5}I KNEW THIS EMERGENCY
BABY MONITOR WOULD
COME IN HANDY.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.292
Portia: Move that here...

16:00.542 --> 16:03.587
We can switch that with this.

16:03.837 --> 16:05.547
MOVING?

16:05.798 --> 16:07.883
SWITCHING THAT AND THIS?

16:07.966 --> 16:11.929
I KNOW I PUT THAT AND THIS
ON THE "DON'T TOUCH" LIST.

16:14.431 --> 16:16.892
{\an3}WE'RE NOT READY FOR
HOUSEKEEPING.

16:16.975 --> 16:18.811
{\an1}HEY, GUYS.

16:19.144 --> 16:21.438
{\an1}SAY, DID I SHOW YOU A LITTLE
TRICK TO THE ESCAPE HATCH?

16:21.689 --> 16:24.650
YOU JUST JIGGLE IT A LITTLE TO
THE LEFT LIKE THIS, AND THEN...

16:24.983 --> 16:28.612
OK, JUST LET ME KNOW WHEN
YOU WANT ME TO... STOP BY.

16:28.862 --> 16:31.699
OK, EVERYTHING'S FINE.

16:31.949 --> 16:35.285
{\an5}YOU'LL GET THE HIVE BACK
IN TWO DAYS, 19 HOURS
AND 55 MINUTES.

16:35.536 --> 16:40.874
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

16:41.125 --> 16:42.459
[GRUNTS]

16:42.710 --> 16:43.836
DRAW ENERGY FROM THE AIR.

16:48.882 --> 16:49.091
[GASPS]

16:55.013 --> 16:56.390
SEE, FINGER?

16:56.640 --> 16:57.766
SAME-SAME, JUST DIFFERENT.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.477
OK, LET'S FOCUS.

17:00.728 --> 17:02.354
BUSINESS AS USUAL.

17:02.604 --> 17:04.356
UH-HUH, UH-HUH, I HEAR YOU.

17:04.606 --> 17:06.775
UH, YEAH, GOOD IDEA, FINGER.

17:06.858 --> 17:08.944
WHY DON'T WE, UH,
BALANCE MY CHECKBOOK?

17:09.028 --> 17:10.945
SEE IF I EARNED ANY INTEREST
ON MY BEE-BUCKS.

17:11.238 --> 17:13.699
ALL RIGHT, LET'S
CRUNCH THE NUMBERS HERE.

17:13.949 --> 17:15.909
ALL RIGHT, CRUNCHING, OK...

17:15.992 --> 17:18.537
CARRY THE ONE, AND THEN
THREE PLUS TWO PLUS...

17:18.787 --> 17:21.165
OH, I CAN'T DO IT,
I CAN'T CONCENTRATE.

17:24.334 --> 17:26.377
BORROW A CUP OF HONEY?

17:26.627 --> 17:28.839
ANYWAY, YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO
BE REMODELING, WOULD YOU?

17:28.922 --> 17:31.508
{\an3}BECAUSE THAT IS A STRICT
VIOLATION OF RULE 518 IN MY...

17:33.469 --> 17:34.136
[GASPS]

17:37.389 --> 17:41.268
OK, ONLY 242 MINUTES TO GO.

17:46.940 --> 17:48.692
WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:48.942 --> 17:50.944
{\an5}WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:51.028 --> 17:52.780
WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:53.030 --> 17:54.782
{\an5}WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:55.032 --> 17:56.909
WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:57.201 --> 17:58.827
{\an5}WHATEVER THEY'VE CHANGED,
I CAN REBUILD.

17:58.911 --> 17:59.536
{\an5}TIME'S UP.

17:58.911 --> 17:59.536
[ALARM CLOCK RINGS]

18:03.040 --> 18:04.958
FRESH TOWELS, PRONTO.

18:05.042 --> 18:07.878
OH, SO I HOPE YOU ENJOYED
YOUR STAY AT THE HIVE...

18:08.128 --> 18:09.588
{\an3}[GRUNTING]

18:09.838 --> 18:11.131
[GASPS]

18:13.592 --> 18:14.635
[GRUNTING...]

18:16.595 --> 18:18.597
[GRUNTING]

18:18.847 --> 18:20.390
[SCREAMS]: WHA?

18:20.474 --> 18:21.266
GASP!

18:26.230 --> 18:28.315
STAY COOL, BESSIE, STAY COOL.

18:28.565 --> 18:30.651
IT'S JUST PAINT AND FURNITURE
AND FEATHERS.

18:30.901 --> 18:32.820
YOU CAN FIX IT LATER.

18:33.070 --> 18:36.490
{\an1}UM, ALL GOOD THINGS
COME TO AN END, SO BYE.

18:36.740 --> 18:38.909
{\an1}PLEASE TURN IN YOUR KEYS AND ANY
COPIES YOU HAVE MADE, THANKS.

18:39.159 --> 18:41.119
OH, THAT, YEAH.

18:41.370 --> 18:43.330
I'M GONNA KEEP IT.

18:43.580 --> 18:44.873
BUT, BUT...

18:45.207 --> 18:46.875
WE HAD A GENTLEMAN'S AGREEMENT.

18:46.959 --> 18:48.293
SO?

18:48.544 --> 18:50.838
I'M A 10-YEAR-OLD GIRL.

18:51.129 --> 18:52.297
{\an6}BRING CLEAN LINENS NEXT TIME,
WE'RE NOT INTO THAT
WATER-SAVING JUNK.

18:55.968 --> 18:57.761
THEY KEEP CALLING ME "GARÇON"

18:58.011 --> 19:00.013
AND DUMPING THEIR LAUNDRY ON ME.

19:00.305 --> 19:01.849
THEY CALL ME PENNY.

19:02.099 --> 19:03.392
AND I GET TO BRING THEM SNACKS.

19:03.642 --> 19:05.102
[GROWLS]

19:05.352 --> 19:07.479
I HEAR YOU, HAPPY.

19:07.729 --> 19:09.064
{\an1}BUT WE CAN'T GET YOUR
BACON OF THE MONTH CLUB PACKAGE

19:09.147 --> 19:10.983
UNTIL WE GET THE HIVE BACK.

19:11.275 --> 19:12.776
{\an1}AND YOU KNOW WHAT, YOU GOTTA
QUIT THAT STUFF, ANYWAY.

19:13.026 --> 19:14.236
{\an3}[BARKS]

19:14.486 --> 19:16.280
[CLEARS THROAT] FRIENDS AND BEN.

19:16.530 --> 19:19.908
{\an1}A CRISIS OF MASSIVE
PROPORTIONS IS AT HAND.

19:19.992 --> 19:22.870
THE HIVE HAS BEEN
ILLEGALLY OCCUPIED.

19:23.203 --> 19:27.332
AND IT IS OUR SWORN DUTY
TO GET RID OF THESE SQUATTERS.

19:27.583 --> 19:29.960
OK, I'M GONNA WHISPER,
BECAUSE EVEN IF THEY CAN'T...

19:30.210 --> 19:33.922
[♪...]

19:35.507 --> 19:36.258
[GROANS]

19:40.178 --> 19:42.848
[♪...]

20:04.620 --> 20:05.787
[PHONE RINGS]

20:06.038 --> 20:07.789
PENNY'S RESIDENCE.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.333
YES, CAN I HELP YOU?

20:09.583 --> 20:11.960
Portia: Penny, popcorn, please.

20:12.211 --> 20:14.129
OH, OK.

20:14.212 --> 20:16.715
PENNY, WHAT WAS THAT?

20:16.965 --> 20:18.967
SHE SAID PLEASE.

20:19.259 --> 20:22.095
Bessie: AW, NUTS,
NOTHING'S WORKING, GUYS.

20:22.387 --> 20:23.972
WE GOTTA THINK
OUTSIDE OF THE BOX.

20:24.056 --> 20:25.891
NEW PLAN, NEW PLAN, NEW PLAN.

20:26.141 --> 20:27.643
YOU'RE A GENIUS,
YOU'RE A GENIUS, BESSIE.

20:30.646 --> 20:31.688
THAT'S IT.

20:31.939 --> 20:33.607
HEY.

20:33.857 --> 20:35.400
QUIET, BEN,
I GOT AN AWESOME IDEA.

20:35.651 --> 20:37.444
{\an1}HAPPY, YOU DRESS UP
AS A SKUNK...

20:37.694 --> 20:40.322
{\an1}SNEAK THROUGH THE DUMBWAITER
AND SCARE 'EM OUT.

20:40.405 --> 20:42.324
[BARKS]

20:42.574 --> 20:44.451
LOOK, HAPPY, DO YOU WANT
YOUR BACON BACK OR NOT?

20:44.701 --> 20:46.954
{\an3}THAT'S WHAT YOU GET
FOR STEALING MY IDEA.

20:47.204 --> 20:48.455
ENJOY YOUR COSTUME.

20:48.705 --> 20:49.206
HMPH. [GROWLS]

20:55.629 --> 20:58.173
[CAT MEOWS]

20:58.256 --> 21:01.093
[BARKS AND HOWLS]

21:01.343 --> 21:02.928
HAPPY?

21:03.178 --> 21:04.179
[MEOWS]

21:04.262 --> 21:05.180
[BARKS]

21:05.430 --> 21:07.557
HAPPY?

21:07.808 --> 21:09.851
HAPPY?

21:10.102 --> 21:11.770
HAPPY.

21:12.020 --> 21:13.271
THE FUTURE OF THE HIVE
IS AT STAKE

21:13.522 --> 21:15.107
AND YOU'RE ENJOYING FINE DINING?

21:15.399 --> 21:17.275
COME ON, LET'S GO.

21:17.526 --> 21:19.569
{\an3}I GOTTA SAY, THOUGH,
YOUR COSTUME LOOKS GREAT.

21:19.820 --> 21:21.488
VERY CONVINCING.

21:21.738 --> 21:23.490
DON'T GIVE ME THAT LOOK, MISTER.

21:23.740 --> 21:27.285
NOW GET YOUR GAME-FACE ON, ROAR.

21:27.536 --> 21:28.787
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

21:29.037 --> 21:30.455
GO GET 'EM, TIGER.

21:30.706 --> 21:32.124
SEE YOU UP THERE.

21:36.003 --> 21:40.632
[PORTIA AND GWEN SCREAM,
SKUNK SNARLS...]

21:44.845 --> 21:46.930
[SCREAMS]

21:47.180 --> 21:49.057
YOU REALLY NEED TO
RETHINK YOUR SCENT.

21:49.141 --> 21:52.686
IT'S TOTALLY NOT WORKING,
WAY TOO MUCH MUSK.

21:52.936 --> 21:54.938
WAY TO GO, HAPPY.

21:52.936 --> 21:54.938
{\an3}[LAUGHS]

21:55.272 --> 21:56.398
[SCREAMING]

21:59.026 --> 22:00.736
GOOD JOB, HAPPY.

22:00.986 --> 22:02.487
I KNEW YOU'D PULL IT OFF.

22:02.738 --> 22:03.238
[GRUNTS]

22:07.993 --> 22:10.996
{\an3}[GASPS] HAPPY MADE
TWO OF HIMSELF.

22:11.329 --> 22:14.332
HAPPY MADE- WAIT, WELL, WHAT?

22:14.583 --> 22:18.253
[GROWLS]

22:18.336 --> 22:22.299
{\an1}[LAUGHS] ISN'T IT GREAT
TO HAVE THE HIVE BACK, HAPPY?

22:23.383 --> 22:28.972
[♪...]

23:03.423 --> 23:07.344
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
